# Laser Flow

Three.js raw WebGL volumetric laser beam with wisp particles and FBM fog simulation, interactive mouse tilt, and adaptive DPR throttling for performance.

## Use when
- Filling a dark hero or landing page background with a dramatic laser beam effect.
- Adding a sci-fi or cyberpunk aesthetic to a product showcase.
- Creating a visually rich interactive demo area.

## Stack
- Framework: react
- Libraries: three

## Install
```bash
npm install three @types/three
```

## Component — laser-flow.tsx
```tsx
// Source: animations_024.md
// Export: LaserFlow (named and default)
// Props: className, style, wispDensity, dpr, mouseSmoothTime, mouseTiltStrength,
//        horizontalBeamOffset, verticalBeamOffset, flowSpeed, verticalSizing,
//        horizontalSizing, fogIntensity, fogScale, wispSpeed, wispIntensity,
//        flowStrength, decay, falloffStart, fogFallSpeed, color
//
// Uses THREE.WebGLRenderer with RawShaderMaterial (custom VERT + FRAG).
// FRAG implements: elliptical beam falloff, arc-length tapping loop,
// vertical wisp lanes with per-lane animation, multi-octave FBM fog,
// mouse-driven tilt, dithering, edge masking, and fade-in.
// Adaptive DPR: samples FPS every 750 ms and scales pixel ratio up/down
// between dprFloor (0.6) and baseDpr to maintain 50-58 fps.
// See full source in raw/animations_024.md
```

## Notes
- Component fills its parent div (`w-full h-full`).
- Requires a container with explicit dimensions.
- Adaptive DPR: automatically reduces resolution if FPS drops below 50.
- `horizontalBeamOffset` shifts the beam left/right as a fraction of width (0.0 = center).
- `color` accepts any CSS hex color string.

## Demo
```tsx
import React from 'react';
import { LaserFlow } from './Component';

export default function App() {
  return (
    <div className="min-h-screen bg-[#1A1A1B] text-white flex flex-col items-center justify-center p-8 font-sans">
      <div className="relative w-full max-w-4xl h-[600px] rounded-3xl overflow-hidden bg-[#060010] border border-white/5">
        <LaserFlow
          horizontalBeamOffset={0.1}
          verticalBeamOffset={0.0}
          color="#FF79C6"
          wispDensity={1.2}
          fogIntensity={0.6}
          className="absolute inset-0 z-0"
        />
        <div className="absolute top-1/2 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 text-center z-10 pointer-events-none">
          <h2 className="text-4xl font-light tracking-widest text-white/90 uppercase mb-2">Energy</h2>
          <p className="text-xs text-white/50 tracking-[0.2em] font-medium">SYSTEM ONLINE</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  );
}
```
